I"øÜ<h2 id="intro">Intro</h2>

<p>There are two things I‚Äôve been meaning to learn how to do:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Access CAISO data</li>
  <li>Make ridgeline plots</li>
</ol>

<p>And so that‚Äôs what I did this weekend, to some success.</p>

<p>I decided to create ridgeline plots, showing the distribution of solar and wind generation within the California Independent System Operator (CAISO) in 2020 across different months. The figure below shows the result for solar PV generation. Ridgeline plots don‚Äôt include y-axes labels ‚Äì these are density plots, so the heights of the curves represent the probably (0-1) of daily generation falling on the corresponding x-axis value. The colors correspond to the mean of daily generation values in each month. So, the darker the red color, the higher the average generation (across a day) within that respective month.</p>

